@startuml
!theme plain
title Cache Read Process with Two Requests (A & B)

' === Participant Definition === '
actor "Request A" as A
actor "Request B" as B
participant "Application Server" as Server
database "Cache" as Cache
database "Database" as DB

skinparam sequence {
    ArrowColor #333
    ActorBorderColor #333
    LifeLineBorderColor #333
    ParticipantBorderColor #333
    DatabaseBorderColor #333
}

' === Flow 1: Request A queries with a cold cache === '
== Request A queries (Cold Cache) ==

A -> Server : Request for post {id}
activate Server

Server -> Cache : Check for key "post:{id}"
activate Cache
Cache --> Server : null (Cache miss)
deactivate Cache

note right of Server #LightYellow
    Not found in cache,
    must query the Database.
end note
Server -> DB : Read post {id} from DB
activate DB
DB --> Server : Return post data
deactivate DB

Server -> Cache : Write post data to cache
activate Cache
Cache --> Server: OK
deactivate Cache

Server --> A : Return post data

... A few seconds later ...

' === Flow 2: Request B queries with a warm cache === '
== Request B queries (Warm Cache) ==

B -> Server : Request for the same post {id}
activate Server

Server -> Cache : Check for key "post:{id}"
activate Cache
Cache --> Server: Return post data (Cache hit)
deactivate Cache

note right of Server #LightGreen
    **Cache Hit!**
    Data is returned immediately
    without querying the Database.
end note

Server --> B : Return post data
deactivate Server

@enduml